1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,576
Welcome to the 6 F’s Protocol Mastery
Practice.

2
00:00:03,576 --> 00:00:10,486
This practice guides you through six
steps for getting to know a part: find,

3
00:00:10,486 --> 00:00:15,000
focus, flesh out, feel toward, befriend,
and fear.

4
00:00:15,000 --> 00:00:16,718
Move slowly.

5
00:00:16,718 --> 00:00:19,597
You do not have to complete every step
perfectly.

6
00:00:19,597 --> 00:00:22,755
Begin by settling into your body.

7
00:00:22,755 --> 00:00:24,984
Take a slow breath in.

8
00:00:33,984 --> 00:00:33,984
<break time="3s" />

9
00:00:33,984 --> 00:00:36,352
And let it out.

10
00:00:36,352 --> 00:00:38,813
The first step is find.

11
00:00:38,813 --> 00:00:44,479
Ask inside: What part of me is asking for
attention right now?

12
00:00:56,479 --> 00:00:56,479
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

13
00:00:56,479 --> 00:00:58,151
Notice one part.

14
00:00:58,151 --> 00:01:05,177
It might appear as a body sensation,
emotion, thought, image, impulse, or

15
00:01:05,177 --> 00:01:05,860
memory.

16
00:01:05,860 --> 00:01:09,297
The second step is focus.

17
00:01:09,297 --> 00:01:12,176
Bring gentle attention to this part.

18
00:01:12,176 --> 00:01:18,445
Not too close. Not too far. Just enough
to notice it.

19
00:01:18,445 --> 00:01:23,878
Ask: Where do I sense this part in or
around my body?

20
00:01:35,878 --> 00:01:35,878
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

21
00:01:35,878 --> 00:01:38,618
The third step is flesh out.

22
00:01:38,618 --> 00:01:40,754
Notice more about the part.

23
00:01:40,754 --> 00:01:51,296
Does it have an image? A shape? A color?
An age? A posture? A voice? A feeling?

24
00:02:03,296 --> 00:02:03,296
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

25
00:02:03,296 --> 00:02:06,686
Let it become more known without forcing.

26
00:02:06,686 --> 00:02:09,519
The fourth step is feel toward.

27
00:02:09,519 --> 00:02:14,627
Ask: How do I feel toward this part?

28
00:02:26,627 --> 00:02:26,627
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

29
00:02:26,627 --> 00:02:30,760
If you feel curious, compassionate, or
calm, notice that.

30
00:02:30,760 --> 00:02:38,446
If you feel angry, afraid, ashamed,
annoyed, or numb, that may be another

31
00:02:38,446 --> 00:02:38,980
part.

32
00:02:38,980 --> 00:02:44,181
Ask that reacting part if it can give you
a little space.

33
00:02:56,181 --> 00:02:56,181
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

34
00:02:56,181 --> 00:02:59,246
Now return to the original part.

35
00:02:59,246 --> 00:03:01,893
The fifth step is befriend.

36
00:03:01,893 --> 00:03:05,562
Let the part know you are not here to get
rid of it.

37
00:03:05,562 --> 00:03:14,429
You might say: I want to understand you.
I know you may be trying to help. I am

38
00:03:14,429 --> 00:03:16,475
willing to listen.

39
00:03:34,475 --> 00:03:34,475
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s"
/><break time="3s" />

40
00:03:34,475 --> 00:03:37,958
Ask: What do you want me to know?

41
00:03:49,958 --> 00:03:49,958
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

42
00:03:49,958 --> 00:03:51,398
Listen.

43
00:04:09,398 --> 00:04:09,398
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s"
/><break time="3s" />

44
00:04:09,398 --> 00:04:12,184
The sixth step is fear.

45
00:04:12,184 --> 00:04:18,639
Ask the part: What are you afraid would
happen if you did not do your job?

46
00:04:30,639 --> 00:04:30,639
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

47
00:04:30,639 --> 00:04:32,682
Listen gently.

48
00:04:32,682 --> 00:04:37,047
This question often reveals what the part
is protecting.

49
00:04:37,047 --> 00:04:38,765
Now thank the part.

50
00:04:38,765 --> 00:04:41,505
You do not have to solve everything.

51
00:04:41,505 --> 00:04:43,827
You have practiced listening.

52
00:04:43,827 --> 00:04:49,075
Ask: What would help you trust me a
little more next time?

53
00:05:01,075 --> 00:05:01,075
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

54
00:05:01,075 --> 00:05:02,375
Listen.

55
00:05:20,375 --> 00:05:20,375
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s"
/><break time="3s" />

56
00:05:20,375 --> 00:05:22,790
Now take a slow breath in.

57
00:05:31,790 --> 00:05:31,790
<break time="3s" />

58
00:05:31,790 --> 00:05:33,555
And let it out.

59
00:05:33,555 --> 00:05:35,459
Return to the room.

60
00:05:44,459 --> 00:05:44,459
<break time="3s" />

61
00:05:44,459 --> 00:05:49,707
Remember: mastery does not mean rushing
through the steps.

62
00:05:49,707 --> 00:05:53,887
Mastery means returning with patience,
respect, and Self-energy.

